goals.question: What is the trend of disasters over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of number of disasters over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the frequency of disasters has increased or decreased over time.

goals.question: What is the most common type of disaster?
goals.visualization: bar chart of disaster types and their frequency
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which type of disaster is most common and therefore requires more attention and resources.

goals.question: What is the distribution of deaths resulting from disasters?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of deaths resulting from disasters and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the number of deaths and the type of disaster?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of number of deaths vs. disaster type
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if certain types of disasters are more deadly than others.

goals.question: What is the trend of deaths resulting from disasters over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of number of deaths over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the number of deaths resulting from disasters has increased or decreased over time.

code:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('Year').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Entity'] = data['Entity'].astype('category')
    disaster_counts = data['Entity'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(disaster_counts.index, disaster_counts.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('Disaster Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common type of disaster?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Deaths'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths resulting from disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
